values:
Silver is ill! &lt;sniff/&gt;

I was about to nip out on Silver this afternoon to head into Oxford to do a little christmas shopping. For some reason, don't quite know why, I decided to look Silver over really thoroughly before I set off. I checked brake fluid levels, tyres, lights, etc and noticed in passing that there was a little pale blue liquid pooled behind one of the webs of the rear hugger moulding, funny I thought, wonder what that is. My inspection continued and I went under the pillion seat cover to check coolant level. A very white looking plastic tank showed itself to me, that's strange I thought, normally there's an appreciable quantity of pale blue liquid sloshing about in there. Two related pieces of information connected in my brain. Damn and blast I have a coolant leak, sure enough looking at the undertray identified a solitary hanging blue drop, of course there was no catching it in the act, the coolant tank was already completely empty. Unfortunately this is a vet job, I could refill it with distilled water and antifreeze, if I had any antifreeze available to me but I don't and in any case I'm discouraged by the idea of allowing money to drip steadily onto the floor. So I'm back without personal transport again until I can get Silver to the vet's, I suspect I may have to say bad and naughty words like warrantee to them. 

He was only three or four hundred miles off his next scheduled service, perhaps it's close enough that I'll can get them to perform that at the same time, but nevertheless...
